This paper is about simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) for robotics, which is a topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper presents a novel spectral learning algorithm, which involves statistical learning and optimization techniques (cs.LG). The algorithm uses range data, which is often processed using computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the algorithm, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the algorithm is applied to a real-world robotic SLAM problem, which involves control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
